<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIMITING SALES OF SPRAY PAINT TO CURB GRAFFITI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have followed with interest the letters and editorials on graffiti. In fact, 
The Times did a story on me and my graffiti-plagued wall. 
</P>
<P>
No mention seems ever to be made of the solution. 
</P>
<P>
There is a San Fernando Valley company called Graffiti Prevention Systems. 
Phone: (800) 247-3395. This company completely solved the problem. 
</P>
<P>
I hired a painter to paint out all graffiti while their serviceman stood by. 
The moment the paint dried the serviceman sprayed on a coat of thin invisible 
wax. 
</P>
<P>
The next morning the wall had been vandalized again. But later in the day 
Graffiti Prevention arrived, steamed off the wax and the wall was pristine 
again. 
</P>
<P>
The first week they had to make several trips. After that word was apparently 
out that vandalism didn't last long on those particular walls. 
</P>
<P>
I paid Graffiti Prevention a monthly fee to be ready to melt off any further 
assaults. I think I needed to call them only once during the next several 
years, before the property was sold. 
</P>
<P>
I do not understand why no mention is ever made of the foolproof solution to 
the problem. 
</P>
<P>
THOMAS L. DAWSON 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
