<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV PLAGIARISM CHARGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It seems clear to me that once CNN reporter Gloria Hillard's material hits the 
network, it's no longer personal property. 
</P>
<P>
Since CNN allows its affiliates to use material from the network without 
restriction, no ethical boundary has been crossed. It is not plagiarism to use 
somebody's material with his or her full consent. 
</P>
<P>
Hillard's indignation is something that should be worked out privately with her 
employer. 
</P>
<P>
W. MARK McKIBBEN 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth 
</P>
</TEXT>
