<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
CHURCH FUND-RAISER TO BENEFIT HOMELESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Santa Ana-based Second Baptist Church will hold its first Homeless Outreach 
fund-raiser and fashion show today to aid some of Orange County's homeless. 
</P>
<P>
The primary goal, project spokesman Donald Craig said, is to collect start-up 
money for the Homeless Outreach Project group to lease property through the 
Department of Housing and Urban Development. 
</P>
<P>
The fund-raiser is from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. at the Newport Beach Marriott Hotel 
and Tennis Club, 900 Newport Center Drive, Newport Beach. For information, call 
the church at (714) 541-4155. 
</P>
</TEXT>
