<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 16-year-old boy was being held Friday in Juvenile Hall on suspicion of 
attempted homicide after shooting his father in the head and stabbing his 
mother in the abdomen and chest, a San Diego police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The boy's name was not released because he is a juvenile. 
</P>
<P>
James Arp, 39, is in serious condition and his wife, Deborah Arp, 38, is in 
critical but stable condition at Mercy Hospital, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
The couple live in the 4400 block of Polk Avenue with their 16-year-old son, a 
12-year-old daughter, and a 5-year-old son. 
</P>
<P>
Details of the incident are sketchy, and police still do not know a motive, 
said police spokesman Bill Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
Officers were called to the house shortly after 6 a.m. Friday. A 9-millimeter 
handgun was found in the house, Robinson said. Police have released no other 
details. 
</P>
